"Supersplicer"
"This large, freaky colored box is a Supersplicer. It will splice big masses you put in at once.\n\nThe first three buttons on the top define what should be spliced. They stand for 'Eggs Only', 'Creatures Only' and 'Both'. The fourth button drops everything.\nWell, 'everything' might be a bit too much said. Actually it drops just the subjects you selected with the 3 buttons before.\nTo pick them up again click somewhere on the base.\n\nThe two input fields in the small box at the top-right are for the mutation settings. The upper field defines the chance on mutation, the lower field how much it should mutate. The valid range is from 0 = nothing happens to 255 = totally freaking out.\n\nIn the box below you see another egg and a norn head. The egg means you'll get your little freak as an egg, the norn head sets the Supersplicer so, that your mutant will given to you as already born creature.\nThe next buttons define the gender. From left to right they are male, female or random.\n\nLast but not least there is the big green button. This is the button which will start the actual splicing process.\n\n\n\nMaybe I should mention here that the 'both'-function only works when there are at least two eggs AND two creatures in..."